The evolution of Linkedin

1. One monolithic application with a DB.
2. Add graph service for storing the relationship of members. This service communicate with the previous application, 
which is a part of role of previous application.
3. The database began to have replicas: one main DB and several replica DB to serve people from different areas.
4. Each section in the previous application was replaced by a new service. Because the site began to have more traffic 
and it is hard to scale based on the old applicaton.
4. Micro services are introduced to hold apis and business logic. The are frontend, mid-tier services, and backend data service.
They also try to use Kafka and Hadoop.
